noun.description: A small tuna with dark horizontal stripes, widely distributed throughout tropical and temperate seas.
A sloop-rigged sailboat with vertical sides and a flat V-shaped bottom, used chiefly on the east coast of the US.

origin: Early 18th century: from the verb skip + jack. skipjack (sense 1) is from the fish's habit of jumping out of the water; skipjack (sense 2, arose in the 19th century.
